$ Shell command usermod: modify a user's account
@ usermod

`usermod` can be used to modify a → Linux/user[user's] account, for example to add a user to a → Linux/fhs/etc/group.

{ Adding a user to a group #add

  A user is added to a group with the `usermod` command:
code {
sudo usermod -aG group-name user-name
code }

}

sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands/useradd[`useradd`] to create a new user.

  → Linux/shell/commands
